@{
    this.ViewData["Title"] = "Privacy Policy";
}
<h1 style="text-align: center;">@this.ViewData["Title"]</h1>

<style>
    div.privacy-box {
        max-height: 70vh; /* Increase height to 70% of the viewport */
        overflow-y: auto;
        padding: 15px;
        border: 1px solid #ccc;
        background-color: #f9f9f9;
        margin-bottom: 20px; /* Reduce margin to bring it closer to the footer */
    }
    </style>

<div class="privacy-box">
    <h2>1. Introduction</h2>
    <p>Welcome to Freedle! Your privacy is important to us, and we are committed to protecting your personal data. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and safeguard the information you provide while using our platform.</p>

    <h2>2. Information We Collect</h2>
    <p>When you use our social media platform, we may collect the following information:</p>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Personal Information:</strong> Your name, email address, phone number, and other details you provide during registration.</li>
        <li><strong>Content:</strong> Posts, comments, photos, videos, and other media you share.</li>
        <li><strong>Technical Data:</strong> IP address, browser type, device information, and cookies used to enhance your experience.</li>
        <li><strong>Interaction Data:</strong> Likes, shares, messages, and interactions with other users.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>3. How We Use Your Information</h2>
    <p>We use the information we collect for the following purposes:</p>
    <ul>
        <li>To provide and improve our platform’s functionality and user experience.</li>
        <li>To personalize content, recommendations, and ads.</li>
        <li>To enhance security, prevent fraud, and enforce our terms.</li>
        <li>To communicate with you about updates, notifications, and support.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>4. Sharing of Information</h2>
    <p>We do not sell your personal data. However, we may share it in the following cases:</p>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>With third-party service providers:</strong> To assist with hosting, analytics, and advertising.</li>
        <li><strong>With law enforcement:</strong> If required by legal obligations or to protect user safety.</li>
        <li><strong>With business partners:</strong> If we engage in mergers, acquisitions, or collaborations.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>5. Data Security</h2>
    <p>We implement security measures to protect your information from unauthorized access, loss, or misuse. However, no method of transmission over the internet is 100% secure.</p>

    <h2>6. Your Rights</h2>
    <p>You have the right to:</p>
    <ul>
        <li>Access, update, or delete your personal data.</li>
        <li>Opt out of targeted ads and marketing communications.</li>
        <li>Request a copy of the data we store about you.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>7. Cookies and Tracking Technologies</h2>
    <p>We use cookies to enhance user experience, analyze traffic, and customize content. You can manage cookie settings in your browser.</p>

    <h2>8. Changes to This Policy</h2>
    <p>We may update this Privacy Policy periodically. We will notify users of significant changes through our platform.</p>

    <h2>9. Contact Us</h2>
    <p>If you have any questions regarding this policy, please contact us at vraychov@tu-sofia.bg.</p>
</div>
